data.name: Password Cracker
data.description:
## INTRO

Let *password* be an n-sized string of ALPHABET. (ALPHABET is given on preloaded script)

```
ALPHABET = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789!#$%&()*+,-./:;<=>?@[]^_`{|}~"
```

Let *test function* be a function which takes a string and checks the given string with predefined password and returns the unit time of the process (not true/false). 

## TASK

Write a function *password_cracker* that takes a test function and finds the password.
You cannot test all ALPHABET with permutation because test cases are huge.

The task has puzzle so all I can give you is "Strings that are not the same length are not the same."

Maximum password size: 250 characters
